{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "cd37357c-c147-40ee-8c97-607433ce6188",
		"name": "H. Reporting & Analytics 📊",
		"description": "# Reporting & Analytics 📊\n\n## Description\n\nUnlock your business data with Amazon's reporting and analytics APIs. This collection provides workflows for generating analytics reports via Data Kiosk and retrieving vendor retail and brand analytics through the Reports API.\n\n## Overview\n\nAmazon provides two main paths for accessing reporting and analytics data through SP-API:\n\n- [<b>Data Kiosk API</b>](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/data-kiosk-api-v2023-11-15-reference) — A GraphQL-based API for querying analytics data. Create queries, check their processing status, and retrieve the resulting documents.\n    \n- [<b>Reports API</b>](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/reports-api-v2021-06-30-reference) — Request and retrieve pre-defined report types covering sales, inventory, fulfillment, and more.\n    \n\n## SP-APIs Involved\n\n| API | Version | Documentation |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Data Kiosk API | v2023-11-15 | [API Reference](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/data-kiosk-api-v2023-11-15-reference) |\n| Reports API | v2021-06-30 | [API Reference](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/reports-api-v2021-06-30-reference) |\n\n## Use Cases\n\n| Folder | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| \\[Data Kiosk Flow\\] Generate Analytics Report | Query and retrieve analytics data using the Data Kiosk API |\n| \\[Reports API\\] Retail and Brand Analytics | Retrieve retail and brand analytics reports |\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- A registered SP-API application ([How to register](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/registering-your-application))\n    \n- Valid SP-API credentials (LWA client ID and secret)\n    \n- A seller or vendor account authorized to your application\n    \n\n### Setup Steps\n\n1. **Fork the collection** — Click \"Fork\" on the collection to create your own copy.\n    \n2. **Fork the environment** — Fork the associated [environment template](https://www.postman.com/amazon-selling-partner-api/sp-api/environment/) as well.\n    \n3. **Set environment variables** — Fill in your `client_id`, `client_secret`, `refresh_token`, `marketplace`, and `base_url` in the environment.\n    \n4. **Assign the environment** — Select the forked environment from the environment dropdown in Postman.\n    \n5. **Start exploring** — The collection includes a pre-request script that automatically handles authentication.\n    \n\n## Additional Resources\n\n- [SP-API Documentation](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/)\n    \n- [Report Type Values](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/report-type-values)\n    \n- [Vendor Analytics Reports](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/report-type-values-analytics)\n    \n- [Data Kiosk Schema Explorer](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/data-kiosk-api-v2023-11-15-use-case-guide)\n    \n- [Marketplace IDs](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/marketplace-ids)",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.0.0/collection.json"
	},
